Repository:
    - Repositories are used to collabrate the work flow
      (tasks) in projects.

    - GitHub is the Open Source Repository
      maintained by google.

    - "Git" is the Tool used to interact with the "GitHub".

Installation Of Git:
--------------------
website   : https://git-scm.com/downloads

file name : Git-2.14.1-64-bit.exe


GitHub Operations:
------------------

1. Create the Repository Locally.

2. Add the User Credentials to the Repository.

3. Create the files to the Repository.

4. Commit the Files to the Repository.

5. Create the Branches

6. Merge the Branches.

7. Integration Of GitHub to the "Visual Studio Code"

8. Commit the Files to Cloud Repository.

9. Push the Code to the Cloud Repository.

10. Pull the Code From Cloud Repository.

11. patches in GitHub.

12. Stash / Unstash Changes

13. Version Comparison

14. Merge Conflict Resolve tool.


Create the Repository Locally.
------------------------------
    - create the directory

        Ex.
            demo

    - launch the "GitBash Here" terminal on
      right click of demo folder.


    - execute the following command

    > git init


[Note : automatically "demo" folder
        converted as local repository]


Add the User Credentials to the Repository.
-------------------------------------------
name:
-----
> git config --global user.name "nareshIT"


email:
------
> git config --global user.email "hr@nareshit.in"


Create the files to the Repository
----------------------------------

> touch sample.html

[Note : Automatically "sample.html" file created in
        Repository with "untracked" mode]


Commit the Files to the Repository
----------------------------------

> git status

    - "red color" labeled files indicated untracked files
       in repository.


> git add sample.html

> git commit

> press "i"

> type "initial commit"

> press "ESC"

> type ":wq"

> press "Enter" key


From 2nd Commit Onwards:
------------------------

> git add sample.ts

> git commit -m "sample code added"



Create the Branch
-----------------
> git branch Angular4

> git checkout Angular4

[Note : Automatically files from the "master branch"
        available to "child branch"(Angular4)]


Merge the Branches
------------------
> git checkout master

> git merge Angular4



Integration Of GitHub to the "Visual Studio Code"
-------------------------------------------------

1. create the account with the GitHub.

    WebSite : https://github.com/join/


2. Download and Install the Visual Studio Code

    Website   : https://code.visualstudio.com/download

    file name : VSCodeSetup-x64-1.16.1.exe


3. Checkout the Code the from the Cloud Repository.

    URL : https://github.com/ajsnaresh/AJS_Classes.git




























































